section
	h2 Hexagonal architecture
	.left(style="font-size: 0.9em;")
		ul
			li Hexagonal architecture pattern, proposed by Dr. Alistair Cockburn in 2005 [1].
			li.fragment Entities (agents) represent core business logic, isolated from external systems.
			li.fragment Ports define interfaces for external communication
			li.fragment Adapters implement ports, translating external data for core logic
